<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-26T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="83" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d83">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/3553: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the President of the League of Nations
                                    Chaco Commission</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Alvarez del Vayo</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-26">February 26, 1934</date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>I thank you sincerely for your courtesy in making available to our
                                Ambassador in Buenos Aires a copy of the draft treaty which your
                                Commission has submitted to the Governments of Bolivia and Paraguay
                                looking to the reestablishment of peace in the Chaco.</p>
                            <p>My earnest hope and that of my Government is that the Commission will
                                be completely successful in these peace efforts.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Cordell Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>